        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 8:42PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 842 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Black Eagle, or near Great Falls, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Fort Benton, Black Eagle, Highwood, Carter, Floweree,
Portage, Malmstrom Afb, Stockett, Tracy, Vaughn, Centerville,
Shonkin, Loma, and Sand Coulee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
